import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['value'] = pd.to_numeric(data['value'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='value', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['value'].median(), color='red', label=f'Median: {data["value"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of budget values across all years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna()
    data = data.sort_values(by=['budgetYear'])
    sns.lineplot(x='budgetYear', y='value', data=data, label='Budget')
    sns.lineplot(x='forecastYear', y='value', data=data, label='Forecast')
    plt.title('How do the budget values compare to the forecast values for each year?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    avg_budget = data.groupby('budgetYear')['value'].mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='budgetYear', y='value', data=avg_budget)
    chart.axhline(avg_budget['value'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Average')
    chart.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.title('What is the average budget value for each year?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna()
    data = data.groupby(['budgetYear', 'forecastYear']).sum().reset_index()
    data = pd.melt(data, id_vars=['budgetYear', 'forecastYear'], value_vars=['value'], var_name='budget_type', value_name='budget_value')
    data['budget_type'] = data['budget_type'].apply(lambda x: 'budget' if x == 'value' else 'forecast')
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.barplot(x="budgetYear", y="budget_value", hue="budget_type", data=data)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    plt.title('How do the budget and forecast values vary across different categories or departments?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
